l demo endpoints. This ensures that security testing is performed only against controlled, development environments and does not affect production or external systems.\n\n## Allowed Endpoints\n\nThe following endpoints are defined in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` and are in scope for ZAP baseline scanning:\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `http://127.0.0.1:8080/` | Local loopback address (IPv4) on port 8080 |\n| `http://localhost:8080/` | Localhost resolution on port 8080 |\n\n## Usage in ZAP Baseline Workflow\n\nThe ZAP baseline scan helper (`scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) validates targets against this allowlist before executing any scans. Any non-local target will be refused with the message \"Refusing non-local target\".\n\n## Policy File Reference\n\nThe authoritative list of in-scope endpoints is maintained in:\n```\npolicy/endpoint_allowlist.yml\n```\n\nWhen adding or removing endpoints, ensure:\n1. The endpoint runs on a local development server\n2. The endpoint is safe for security testing\n3. The documentation is updated accordingly\n4. The validation commands continue to pass", "message": "docs: enhance endpoint allowlist documentation for ZAP baseline workflow", "branch": "main"}, "id": "call_a9b47014de8b416c9bd13cc9", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9525, "output_tokens": 1010, "total_tokens": 10535, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8896}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 482}}}}]}}}
