{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:40:22.468848+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, I'm unable to push changes directly to the repository due to permission limitations with the current GitHub token (403 error). However, I have a clear understanding of what Issue #5 requires and can provide the exact changes needed.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Changes for Issue #5\n\n**Issue #5** requests adding endpoint allowlist documentation. The two files that need to be updated are:\n\n### 1. `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md`\n\nReplace the current minimal content with comprehensive documentation:\n\n```markdown\n# In-Scope Endpoints\n\nThis document describes the endpoints that are intentionally in scope for the ZAP baseline security scanning workflow.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe ZAP baseline scan is configured to only target local demo endpoints. This ensures that security testing is performed only against controlled, development environments and does not affect production or external systems.\n\n## Allowed Endpoints\n\nThe following endpoints are defined in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` and are in scope for ZAP baseline scanning:\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `http://127.0.0.1:8080/` | Local loopback address (IPv4) on port 8080 |\n| `http://localhost:8080/` | Localhost resolution on port 8080 |\n\n## Usage in ZAP Baseline Workflow\n\nThe ZAP baseline scan helper (`scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) validates targets against this allowlist before executing any scans. Any non-local target will be refused with the message \"Refusing non-local target\".\n\n## Policy File Reference\n\nThe authoritative list of in-scope endpoints is maintained in:\n```\npolicy/endpoint_allowlist.yml\n```\n\nWhen adding or removing endpoints, ensure:\n1. The endpoint runs on a local development server\n2. The endpoint is safe for security testing\n3. The documentation is updated accordingly\n4. The validation commands continue to pass\n```\n\n### 2. `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml`\n\nAdd header comments to make the file self-documenting:\n\n```yaml\n# Endpoint Allowlist for ZAP Baseline Scanning\n#\n# Only local demo endpoints are in scope for security scanning.\n# Non-local targets will be rejected by the scan helper.\n\nin_scope:\n  # Local demo application running on the loopback address\n  - http://127.0.0.1:8080/\n  - http://localhost:8080/\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nAfter applying these changes, running `make validate` will continue to pass because:\n- No required files are being removed\n- The validation script checks for specific files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `zap/baseline.conf`, `sample_data/zap_baseline.json`, `scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) and that `run_zap_baseline.sh` contains \"Refusing non-local target\"\n- These changes are documentation-only and don't affect the validation logic\n\nTo apply these changes, you would need to grant write permissions to the repository or have a user with appropriate access commit these files.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 694, "prompt_tokens": 11207, "total_tokens": 11901, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 62, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10560, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000314468, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000120148, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00019432}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780875612-2M0vGq9dkggCFIZP88DR", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea475-4f31-7542-a5ba-c27f47c79f6d-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11207, "outp